- feature_033: adjusted coefficient -8.490e-4, p=5.95e-6.

The main-effect evidence was not uniform. Iteration 3 intentionally tested near-null features; those hypotheses were not supported, with signed effects close to zero and nonsignificant p-values. This helped separate a smaller set of reproducible predictors from features with little marginal signal.

Strongest binary-binary subgroup interactions:
- feature_015 x feature_025: interaction 0.192574 (19.26 percentage points), p=<1e-300; cell rates 00=0.1679, 10=0.1663, 01=0.1585, 11=0.3495.
